    "type" :
    
    
    "list"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "items" : [
    
    
    
    "Ultra-high-strength body parts must only be replaced as a complete unit."
    ,
    
    
    "Ultra-high-strength body parts can no longer be reshaped."
    ,
    
    
    "Straightening and reshaping is not permitted. "
    ,
    
    
    "Use special drill bits for drilling ultra-high-strength steel."
    ,
    
    
    "Resistance spot-welding can only be carried out using the inverter welders currently approved by Porsche AG."
    ,
    
    
    "Plug spot-welding ultra-high-strength steel does not produce sufficiently strong joints. If holes need to be welded, additional welding seams must be applied."
    ,
    
    
    "For butt, overlap and reinforcement welding, the individual spot welds and welded seams must be at least 30 mm long."
    ,
    
    
    "Resistance spotwelds can also be replaced by blind rivets and adhesive. The number of rivets must be increased for ultra-high-strength steel panels."
    
    ]
    
    }
    
